Here is the full summary of all comments found in staged TypeScript/TSX/JS files.

---

**1. `.storybook/addons/json-editor/CodeMirrorEditor.tsx`** (line 391)
```
// eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps
```

**2. `.storybook/addons/json-editor/JsonEditorPanel.tsx`** (line 125)
```
// eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps
```

**3. `.storybook/addons/json-editor/sduiSnippets.ts`** (lines 10, 132, 148)
```
// ─── Components ──────────────────────────────────────────
// ─── Structure ───────────────────────────────────────────
// ─── Screen Templates ───────────────────────────────────
```

**4. `.storybook/decorators/PhoneFrameDecorator.tsx`** (lines 118-130)
```
// phoneDevice: {
//   name: 'Device',
//   description: 'Select phone device size',
//   toolbar: {
//     icon: 'grow',
//     title: 'Device',
//     items: Object.entries(DEVICES).map(([key, device]) => ({
//       value: key,
//       title: `${device.name} (${device.width}×${device.height})`,
//     })),
//     dynamicTitle: true,
//   },
// },
```
This is **commented-out dead code** -- a full toolbar config block.

**5. `.storybook/main.ts`** (lines 68, 93, 208, 213, 218, 279)
```
// not a .d.ts, let Vite handle it normally
// file not readable, fall through to default stub
// Ubuntu fonts from design system (Ubuntu-*.ttf)
// Icon fonts (IconsSemParar, icomoon) + other local fonts — overrides DS on name collision
// Figma design tiles for comparison dashboard
// Native module mocks (no ~/ aliases here — handled by tildeResolverPlugin)
```

**6. `src/services/sdui/adapters/index.ts`** (lines 28-29)
```
// FIXME: use something like "props: DUIProps<Foo, Bar>" during component
//  creation in order to avoid eliminate the use of "as SDUIComponentRenderer"
```
This is a **FIXME** -- a known tech debt item.

**7. `src/services/sdui/models/index.ts`** (lines 15, 141, 158, 172)
```
// ---- 3.5  JSON Logic (subset) --------------------------------------------
// ---- 3.1  Screen Structure ------------------------------------------------
// ---- Component Registry ---------------------------------------------------
// ---- Known Component Types (voucher screens) ------------------------------
```
Plus JSDoc blocks at lines 17-20 and 64-68:
```ts
/**
 * Accesses a value from the context using dot notation.
 * @example { var: 'balance.pointsFormatted' }
 */
```
```ts
/**
 * A boolean value computed from a JSON Logic rule.
 * Used for visibility, enabled state, or any boolean prop.
 * @example { rule: { '>': [{ var: 'form.points' }, 0] } }
 */
```

**8. `src/services/sdui/renderer/FallbackComponent.tsx`** (lines 10-14)
```ts
/**
 * Dev-only fallback for unregistered SDUI component types.
 * Uses RN primitives intentionally — DS components require ThemeProvider
 * which may not be available in all rendering contexts (tests, error boundaries).
 */
```

**9. `src/services/sdui/renderer/ScreenRenderer.test.tsx`** (line 364)
```
// Press should not throw even without actionRegistry
```

**10. `src/services/sdui/utils/jsonLogic.test.ts`** (lines 455, 533-536, 541-542)
```
// (points * 0.01) + 10
// Build deeply nested: +(+(+(... 1, 1), 1), 1) — 25 levels deep
// At depth > 20, computeArithmetic returns 0
// Inner levels that exceed depth return 0, so the deepest operand
// resolves to 0 instead of its true value, capping computation
// Without depth limit: 2000 + 25*1000 = 27000
// With depth limit at 20: innermost levels return 0, so result < 27000
```

---

**Summary by category:**

| Category | Files | Action suggested |
|---|---|---|
| **eslint-disable directives** | `CodeMirrorEditor.tsx`, `JsonEditorPanel.tsx` | Acceptable (necessary suppressions) |
| **Section dividers** | `sduiSnippets.ts`, `models/index.ts` | Acceptable (structural navigation aids) |
| **Commented-out dead code** | `PhoneFrameDecorator.tsx` (lines 118-130) | Should be removed |
| **Config/build clarifications** | `.storybook/main.ts` (6 comments) | Acceptable (build config is legitimately complex) |
| **FIXME / tech debt** | `src/services/sdui/adapters/index.ts` (lines 28-29) | Track in backlog, remove or resolve |
| **JSDoc documentation** | `models/index.ts`, `FallbackComponent.tsx` | Good -- keep per CLAUDE.md style guide |
| **Test clarifications** | `ScreenRenderer.test.tsx`, `jsonLogic.test.ts` | Acceptable in test files for intent clarity |

The two items most worth addressing are the **commented-out dead code** in `PhoneFrameDecorator.tsx` and the **FIXME** in `src/services/sdui/adapters/index.ts`.

